parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Failure Due to Ruptured Brake Line

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine module can cause engine failure, leading to costly repairs and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the thermostat can cause engine overheating, leading to engine damage and potentially leaving the driver stranded.
The failure of the front wheel bearing can cause the wheel to lock up, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries.
